# CAST — Claude Agent Specialist Team

Tech stack, projects, and conventions are in `~/.claude/rules/`.

---

## Hook Directives (MANDATORY)

System hooks inject directives into your context. These are not suggestions — follow them immediately.

- **`[CAST-DISPATCH]`** — Dispatch the named agent via the Agent tool. Pass the user's full prompt. Do NOT handle the task inline.
- **`[CAST-REVIEW]`** — Dispatch `code-reviewer` (haiku) after completing your current logical unit of changes.
- **`[CAST-CHAIN]`** — After the primary agent completes, dispatch the listed agents in sequence. Do not ask for confirmation.
- **Agent Work Logs** — When an agent returns a `## Work Log` section, echo it verbatim to the user before continuing. Do not summarize or collapse it. This is the user's primary visibility into what happened.
- **`[CAST-DISPATCH-GROUP: <group-id>]`** — Auto-generate an Agent Dispatch Manifest
  from the Payload JSON in the directive. Pass immediately to orchestrator with no
  approval gate. Orchestrator runs waves in order: parallel agents fire simultaneously,
  Fan-out Summary is prepended to the next wave's prompts, post_chain agents run
  sequentially after all waves complete.
  Do NOT ask for confirmation. Do NOT handle inline. Do NOT skip orchestrator.

---

## Inline Whitelist

You handle these directly — everything else goes to an agent:
- Read and analyze code (never modifying)
- Answer questions about the codebase
- Orchestrate agent dispatches and post-chains
- Conversation with the user
- Documentation edits (non-code: .md, .txt, comments-only) under 10 lines

CODE CHANGES — even single-line fixes — go to `code-writer` or the appropriate specialist
agent. The rule: if it modifies executable behavior, it is NOT inline. No exceptions for
"small" changes. When in doubt, dispatch.

